"""
=============================================================================
EchoPrime Evaluator v6.0 — Multi-Threshold Trials
=============================================================================
Runs 5 evaluation trials per feature, each with a different threshold-selection
strategy. AUROC and AUPRC are threshold-independent and computed once per
feature; Sensitivity / Specificity / PPV / NPV / Confusion Matrix depend on
the operating point and are recomputed per trial.

Trials:
  1. Youden's J        — argmax(TPR − FPR) on the ROC curve
  2. Sensitivity ≥ 90% — lowest threshold satisfying sens ≥ 0.90
  3. Sensitivity ≥ 95% — lowest threshold satisfying sens ≥ 0.95
  4. Specificity ≥ 90% — highest threshold satisfying spec ≥ 0.90
  5. Specificity ≥ 95% — highest threshold satisfying spec ≥ 0.95

Per binary feature (17 cardiac features):
  - AUROC with 95% CI  (bootstrap, 10,000 iterations) — once
  - AUPRC with 95% CI  (bootstrap, 10,000 iterations) — once
  - Per-trial: chosen threshold, Sens / Spec / PPV / NPV with 95% CI,
    confusion matrix (TP/FP/TN/FN), and confusion-matrix heatmap.

Outputs:
  - One Excel workbook with one Summary sheet per trial + a Full_Metrics
    sheet per trial + a Thresholds sheet listing all chosen operating points.
  - ROC curve per feature (with all 5 operating points marked) — once.
  - PR curve per feature — once.
  - Confusion matrix per (feature × trial) — 17 × 5 = 85 plots.
=============================================================================
"""

